IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: IMPROVING THE LIVING CONDITIONS OF LOW INCOME FAMILIES THROUGH HOUSING AND COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT.
IRS990.MissionDescription: IMPROVING THE LIVING CONDITIONS OF LOW INCOME FAMILIES THROUGH HOUSING AND COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT.
IRS990.Description: SELF-HELP HOUSING - ASSISTED 91 FAMILIES IN COMPLETING THE CONSTRUCTION OF THEIR NEW HOMES. 26 OTHER HOMES WERE IN THE PROCESS OF CONSTRUCTION AS OF JUNE 30, 2010. APPROXIMATELY 40 APPLICANT HOUSEHOLDS WERE IN THE PRE-PRODUCTION PHASE WHICH INCLUDES LOAN APPLICATION, QUALIFICATION, UNDERWRITING, AND HOMEOWNERSHIP EDUCATION.HOMEBUYER ASSISTANCE PROGRAM - 77 FAMILIES RECEIVED SECONDARY MORTGAGE FINANCING TO HELP THEM PURCHASE HOMES.REHABILITATION - 93 FAMILIES RECEIVED FINANCING AND ASSISTANCE IN THE REHABILITATION OR RECONSTRUCTION OF THEIR HOMES.MULTIFAMILY HOUSING - 1,154 LOW INCOME HOUSING FAMILIES RESIDE IN 23 AFFORDABLE RENTAL HOUSING PROJECTS DEVELOPED AND SPONSORED BY SELF-HELP ENTERPRISES. TWO PROJECTS (104 APARTMENTS) ARE IN THE DEVELOPMENT PIPELINE. EACH PROJECT PROVIDES A RANGE OF RESIDENT SERVICES SUCH AS CHILD CARE, COMPUTER LABS, AND ESL CLASSES.COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT - ASSISTANCE TO SMALL COMMUNITIES WITH SEWER AND WATER PROBLEMS IS ONGOING WITH WORK BEING DONE IN MORE THAN 50 SMALL RURAL COMMUNITIES. OVER 1,500 NEW RESIDENTIAL SEWER OR WATER CONNECTIONS WERE COMPLETED.HOMEOWNERSHIP EDUCATION AND COUNSELING - 1,361 LOW INCOME HOUSEHOLDS RECEIVED INDIVIDUAL AND/OR CLASSROOM HOMEOWNERSHIP TRAINING AND 1,032 HOMEOWNERS RECEIVED FORECLOSURE MITIGATION COUNSELING.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The CEO's salary is established under the terms of a 5 year contract which fixes compensation for the contract term. Contract terms were determined based on a review of comparable Form 990's and survey information from peer organizations. The Board and/or Executive Committee establishes compensation ranges for all other officers and key employees within established ranges set by the Board and/or Executive Committee action. All ranges are determined based on a combination of information from Form 990's available on Guidestar, targeted compensation surveys, and internal assessment of retention and hiring experience.
